---
title: Crispy BBQ Cauliflower Naan Wraps with Pickle Slaw & Potato Chips
description: What’s not to love about vegetarian naan wraps packed with crispy fried cauliflower and a ton of backyard BBQ flavor? Along with the BBQ-spiced cauliflower, you’ll stuff these wraps with a tangy pickle slaw that brings a fresh crunch to each bite. Complete the meal with a drizzle of creamy BBQ sauce and a side of potato chips.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/686beb535ba155634794fc41-40b77b7c.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/686beb535ba155634794fc41-en-US.pdf
nutrition:
  calories: 1170 kcal
  fat: 53 g
  saturated fat: 11 g
  carbohydrates: 147 g
  sugar: 43 g
  protein: 20 g
  fiber: 9 g
  sodium: 2780 mg
author: Michelle Doll Olson
course: main course
time required: 35 minutes
cuisine: North America
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/crispy-bbq-cauliflower-naan-wraps-686beb535ba155634794fc41
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry produce.

Roughly chop @dill pickle{1}(sliced). Cut @cauliflower florets{10%oz} into 1-inch pieces.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine @red cabbage and carrot mix{8%oz}, chopped pickle, @sour cream{1.5%tbsp}, half the @mayonnaise{4%tbsp}, ½ tsp @sugar{½%tsp} (1 tsp for 4 servings), @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{pinch}.

In a #small bowl{}, whisk together @BBQ sauce{½%cup} and remaining mayonnaise.

In a #large bowl{}, whisk together @tempura batter{82%g}, @sweet and smoky BBQ seasoning{1%tbsp}, half the @cumin{1%tsp}, @water{⅓%cup}, and a pinch of salt and pepper (all the cumin and ⅔ cup water for 4 servings).

> TIP: If mixture seems too thick, add more water 1 tsp at a time until it reaches a pancake-batter-like consistency.

Stir in cauliflower until fully coated.

Heat a ⅓-inch layer of @cooking oil{} in a #large, preferably heavy-bottomed pan{} over medium-high heat. Once oil is hot enough that a drop of batter sizzles when added to the pan, using a #slotted spoon{}, add coated cauliflower.

> TIP: Don't overcrowd the pan! You'll need to work in batches.

Cook until cauliflower is golden brown and crisp, ~{2-3%minutes} per side. Using a slotted spoon, transfer to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}. Immediately season with a pinch of salt.

Wrap @naan bread{2} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Divide naan, flat sides up, between plates; evenly spread each piece with 2 TBSP creamy BBQ sauce. Fill with as much pickle slaw as you like; top with crispy cauliflower. Drizzle with remaining creamy BBQ sauce to taste. Fold naan in half over filling (like a taco!).

Serve naan wraps with @potato chips{1}, any remaining pickle slaw, and any remaining creamy BBQ sauce on the side for dipping.